com.team1389.hardware.outputs.hardware

Class CANTalonHardware

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team1389.hardware.Hardware<CAN>
      • com.team1389.hardware.outputs.hardware.CANTalonHardware
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompositeWatchable, Watchable

    public class CANTalonHardware
extends Hardware<CAN>
    This class offers input/output stream sources for a Talon SRX.

    Furthermore, this class will ensure that the Talon has been given all required configuration before it enters any control mode.
    TODO add limit switch support

    Author:
    amind

      • getSpeedInput

        public RangeIn<Speed> getSpeedInput()
        Returns:
        a speed input stream indicating the current speed of the motor based on the talon's preferred speed sensor
        uses a default range of [0,1023] specified by the talon manual, but may vary depending on the speed sensor

      • getPositionInput

        public RangeIn<Position> getPositionInput()
        Returns:
        a position input stream indicating the current speed of the motor based on the talon's preferred position sensor
        uses a default range of [0,8192] specified by the Vex versaplanetary encoder, but may vary depending on the sensor
